cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.CV

The paper deals with the problem of extracting and querying tabular data from PDF documents, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed solution involves the use of deep learning techniques (cs.DL) for table type classification and header matching, as well as database query processing (cs.DB) for nearest row search. Finally, the paper also mentions the use of computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for table detection and extraction.
